Wire FCM push dispatch + Devices API + project push toggles UI

Backend:
- Add /api/v1/devices/{register,unregister} endpoints for Flutter to
  store/revoke FCM tokens (scoped to current tenant + user).
- Dispatch push events at the same callsites as email notifications:
  AgentJobProcessor (ContentGenerated), PublishContentCommandHandler
  and CalendarPublishBackgroundService (ContentPublished),
  ApproveContentCommandHandler (ApprovalNeeded).
- FcmPushNotificationService now stamps TenantId on newly-registered
  device tokens via ITenantContext.
- Extend ProjectDto + GetProjectByIdQueryHandler and the
  /email-notifications PUT endpoint/request to accept
  NotifyPushOn{Generation,Publication,ApprovalNeeded} flags.

Frontend:
- Rename the email-notifications card to "Notifiche" and add a Push
  mobile section with toggles for the three events.
- Add the three push flags to the Project type.

All three push flags are opt-in (default false). Frontend keeps sending
them on each save so persistence is deterministic.
